HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 775
By Lynn
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the Mt. Juliet Police
Department upon the opening of its new
headquarters.
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee is blessed with dedicated law enforcement officers
who risk their personal safety, even their lives, to protect and serve their communities; and
WHEREAS, one such group is the Mt. Juliet Police Department, whose new
headquarters opened for public use on November 24, 2025; and
WHEREAS, located adjacent to Charlie Daniels Park, the new police headquarters is a
$34 million, 54,000-square-foot edifice that will provide more space to accommodate the
department's growth and be more fortified for emergencies; and
WHEREAS, the building includes vital facilities, such as a new crime lab, a larger
evidence facility, and a K-9 bathtub, as well as a "Chief's Coffee Corner" and tornado shelter for
the community; and
WHEREAS, the department now houses their emergency response team in the building
along with the return of their investigation unit, which had not been in the same building for the
previous six years; and
WHEREAS, the process of transitioning to the new headquarters came in two phases.
Phase one of moving to the new headquarters included relocating administration, patrol,
investigations, and records departments; phase two involved dispatch and emergency
communications; and
WHEREAS, Mt. Juliet Deputy Chief Tyler Chandler oversaw the new headquarters,
taking on the role of project manager and gathering input from staff; and
HJR0775
011406
- 1 -

WHEREAS, on this special occasion, we wish to extend our gratitude and approbation to
the Mt. Juliet Police Department for making the State of Tennessee a safer place to live; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Mt. Juliet Police Department on the
opening of its new headquarters, extending our deepest gratitude for the dedication of
members, past and present, to protecting and serving the citizens of Mt. Juliet and this State.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
